Games
Coming soon
Watch Trailer
Welcome to Elynd, a world struggling to survive in the wake of the Great Flood.
As a deadly plastification threatens to kill all living things, steel yourself to face the numerous challenges posed by this ocean planet.
Find a cure, explore floating platforms, or deal with the threats exposed by the community.
As you delve deeper into the mysteries of Elynd, you’ll never be alone…
2023
Watch Trailer
Produced in 2023, is the prequel to Road 96, with an atypical and colorful identity.
With third-person musical sequences and First Person narrative adventures, the player make their own choices which will have big consequences on the destiny of the two characters you play: Kaito and Zoe.
2021
Watch Trailer
Released in August 2021. During this narrative road trip, the player plays teenagers who are fleeing the poverty of their country.
They​ hope to cross the border to find a better life. During their journey, they meet key characters, and discover part of their lives and their secrets. This critically acclaimed project received 5 Pégases, including that for narrative excellence and is a huge commercial success.
2018
Watch Trailer
Created in 2018, deals with the First World War. The idea is to show the war from another prism.
This game, collected two​ nominations for the prestigious BAFTAs as well as a nomination in the Games For Impact category at The Game Awards.
2016
Watch Trailer
Released in 2016, addresses mutual aid through the relationship between the hero Kaito and his friend Aya, but also illness in order to make the player aware of the cancer that the hero's friend suffers from.
The game was acclaimed by Apple and Google, and was named one of the best mobile games of 2016.
Values
We are committed to creating a respectful work environment, where all employees are treated with fairness and dignity.​
Creative
DigixArt seeks to demonstrate innovation and creativity in the design of its games. The company is constantly looking for new ways to bring fresh ideas and originality to the field of video games.
Humble
The studio recognizes that every project is an opportunity to learn and grow, and considers mistakes, iterations and difficulties to be part of this learning process.
Reliable
Respecting deadlines and commitments is essential at DigixArt.The company is committed to providing a stable and secure working environment for its employees, as well as to respecting the commitments it makes with its partners and customers.
At DigixArt, we believe in an inclusive company culture, where everyone is encouraged to express their ideas and contribute to the success of the company. We value integrity, teamwork, creativity and passion for video games.
Career
Work with us
Flexible working hours, to allow you to better reconcile your professional and personal life
“Spanish Fridays” where we leave at 4pm
Remote work possible twice a week (Tuesday & Thursday)​
Training and professional development opportunities to help you progress in your career.
Quarterly corporate events, beach, mountains and city center are just minutes away​
Complete health coverage covered 50% by the company
Lunch vouchers, free fruits, coffee and moreover free video games from PLAION group
